 I wonder if there was a mistake there.

83
00:03:56,780 --> 00:03:58,700
 Yeah, I probably need to edit this file.

84
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,100
 Maybe when you look at this file it won't be there.

85
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:01,940
 Oh, that's not, maybe I'll leave it there.

86
00:04:01,940 --> 00:04:02,980
 That's pretty cool.

87
00:04:02,980 --> 00:04:05,260
 Now here's another thing.

88
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:08,700
 So this DELETE TO USERS, if I run it again,

89
00:04:08,700 --> 00:04:10,220
 it's not really an error.

90
00:04:10,220 --> 00:04:13,620
 If I see there's nothing deleted,

91
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:16,540
 because I expressed a thing, a thing about SQL.

92
00:04:16,540 --> 00:04:19,540
 When I said DELETE ALL THE RECORDS FROM USERS

93
00:04:19,540 --> 00:04:23,340
 where this is true, and there were none for which it was true,

94
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:24,260
 that's just fine.

95
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:26,360
 I could say, you know,

96
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:32,900
 or email equals that @blatt.that.

97
